Saturday August 24th 2013 2:03 pm -04:00,Hi GunesIm brand new at programming so I can only tell you what my understanding of the video lecture is.Integer division denoted by the operator // (not / as you wrote above) gives you only the whole number part of the answer.  Two is the whole number part of the answer.  Since 12 divided by 5 equals 2 2/5 (two and two fifths) two is the whole part of the number and the two fifths is a fraction that is left off.  Presumably its because integers are positive and negative whole numbers (plus zero) and therefore since were doing integer division the program returns an integer answer.  Perhaps someone who knows more about programming could confirm that?Hope this helps and good luck!, Resolved,0
