Thursday September 26th 2013 7:18 pm -04:00,EtienneThank you.  I came up with the following code with all your hand holding.  It seems to be working.  I used len(of_the_input) instead of 10 because I thought the number could be different lengths based  one whether country or area codes are entered.def valid_phone_number():        phone_num = input(Enter your phone number: )    chars_in_phone = 0            for char in phone_num:        if char not in 0123456789-:            return Invalid phone number        if char.isdigit() or char == -:            chars_in_phone = chars_in_phone + 1    if chars_in_phone == len(phone_num):        return Valid phone number(I know the second if statement could have been the opposite of the first.)Feel free to let me know how I can improve it.Shannon,None,0
